				An idea zajeer may like -- Give the follow two options for raid level charm augs:<br><br>1) Have charm flags added to normal raid level augs.<br><br>2) Create a quest similar to BiC to make the best charm aug.&nbsp; Have it be considerably powerful after the last groupable/mini raid stage, but require parts from high end raids to take it to the point where it's better than the augs you normally get from raids. <br><br>Example:<br>
Quested up to mini raid level (comparable step 10 bic) - 125 hp mana&nbsp; 2% spell&nbsp; shield / dot shield<br>
Raid aug (non-quest) -&nbsp; 175 hp mana 3% spell shield / dot shield<br>
Fully powered quested aug (multiple items from high end raids needed) - 225 hp mana 4% spell shield / dot shield<br><br>This way any raider, regardless of out-of-raid playtime, can have access to raid level charm augs.&nbsp; But raiders who are willing to put in effort outside of raids can get something that's a step above.&nbsp; This also gives non-high end raiders a shot at a considerable upgrade, if they're willing to put the effort into it.<div></div><br><br>
				
